Package com.example.diningapp

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BuildConfig  
    Cafe
    This class is an eatery, an instance representation of a store, cafe, or other non-dining hall eatery on Cornell campus.
    CafeActivity
    A cafe, not accepting meal swipes, has a static menu.
    DiningList
    Creates a list of all eateries from the MasterEateryList.
    DiningListAdapter
    This ArrayAdapter is used to populate the ListViews in the DiningList.
    Eatery
    This abstract class is a superclass of both Hall and Cafe, and represents a place to eat on Cornell campus Fields are used to populate both the listView and the Eatery's corresponding activity.
    Hall
    This class is an Dining Hall, an instance representation of an All You Care to Eat dining hall on Cornell Campus.
    HallActivity
    Creates a Hall, an All You Care To Eat eatery from data in the MasterEateryList This class populates static items (logo, description, containers) in the same thread, but uses AsyncTasks to get and set items that need to be grabbed online (menus and schedules)
    HoursRequester
    An AsyncTask that grabs schedule information from the Cornell servers then returns that that the Hall class Information is grabbed from a Google Calendar using JSoup and put into clean times.
    MasterEateryList
    A singleton that retrieves data from eatery_data.txt and stores it for use by various activities
    MenuRequester
    Scrapes the cornell webserver using a POST request to get menu data

    Settings
    Settings class - stores, changes, manages, and listens for settings changes in the app Takes appropriate action when settings are changed as well
    Settings.SettingsFragment
    The settings fragment for this app
